host:   AMD Ryzen 9 7950X (Zen 4, water-cooled, 128 GB DDR5)
cmd:    cargo bench --bench deinterleave --features experimental
zenbench: 0.1.7
date:   2026-04-29 UTC
notes:
  - 5 rounds × ~22 calls each (zenbench auto-converged at "noisy" stop, 27-32% CV)
  - Throughput "iB/s" column in zenbench output appears miscalibrated (orders of
    magnitude too large); trust the ns timings and compute B/s manually.
  - At 16 MP (RGB24 → 192 MB output) both paths are DRAM-write-bandwidth-bound.
    SIMD compute speedup only visible while the working set fits in L3 (≤ ~1 MP).
